The paper presents a novel hashing strategy for approximate furthest neighbor search, which is a problem commonly encountered in computer science and machine learning. The paper discusses the behavior of the furthest neighbor search problem and presents an algorithm that outperforms existing strategies. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
